# Chart axis standards

Applies to **every chart** produced in this project (matplotlib report scripts, findings
graphs, signal charts, deck visuals).

1. **Y-axis units follow the metric.**
   - **Percentage / rate** series (take rate, retention %, conversion): format Y ticks as
     percentages (e.g. `20%`, `30%`) — use `matplotlib.ticker.PercentFormatter`.
   - **Count / quantity** series (acquisition volume, new customers, any quantity):
     plain integer numbers. **Never label a count as a percentage.**
2. **Y-axis starts at 0.** The maximum keeps auto-scaling to the data (do not cap the
   max). Applies to both line and bar charts.
3. **Do not plot metrics with very different scales/levels on the same chart** (e.g. a
   first-period and a later-period retention together) — combined trends become
   unreadable. One chart per series/level.
